<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="93" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,1587,1867]" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,274,1587,1614]" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
The absence of obvious synapomorphies has hampered the delimitation of the genus 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1873" box="[1289,1436,1588,1614]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Tetrablemma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1289,1436,1588,1614]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">Tetrablemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lehtinen, P. T." box="[159,333,1624,1650]" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref5329" refString="Lehtinen, P. T. (1981) Spiders of the Oriental-Australian region. III. Tetrablemmidae, with a world revision. Acta Zoologica Fennica, 162, 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="1981">Lehtinen, 1981</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation author="Tong, Y. &amp; Li, S." box="[345,538,1624,1651]" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" pagination="84 - 98" refId="ref5600" refString="Tong, Y. &amp; Li, S. (2008) Tetrablemmidae (Arachnida, Araneae), a spider family newly recorded from China. Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution, 8 (2), 84 - 98. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ode. 2007.01.002" type="journal article" year="2008">Tong &amp; Li, 2008</bibRefCitation>
). According to 
<bibRefCitation author="Tong, Y. &amp; Li, S." box="[708,911,1624,1651]" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" pagination="84 - 98" refId="ref5600" refString="Tong, Y. &amp; Li, S. (2008) Tetrablemmidae (Arachnida, Araneae), a spider family newly recorded from China. Organisms Diversity &amp; Evolution, 8 (2), 84 - 98. https: // doi. org / 10.1016 / j. ode. 2007.01.002" type="journal article" year="2008">Tong &amp; Li (2008)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1873" box="[922,1069,1624,1650]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Tetrablemma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[922,1069,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">Tetrablemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is closely related to 
<taxonomicName authority="Lehtinen, 1981" authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1981" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Singalangia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1301,1436,1624,1650]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">Singalangia</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lehtinen, P. T." box="[151,320,1660,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref5329" refString="Lehtinen, P. T. (1981) Spiders of the Oriental-Australian region. III. Tetrablemmidae, with a world revision. Acta Zoologica Fennica, 162, 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="1981">Lehtinen, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName authority="Lehtinen, 1981" authorityName="Lehtinen" authorityYear="1981" box="[374,708,1660,1686]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Rhinoblemma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[374,530,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">Rhinoblemma</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Lehtinen, P. T." box="[536,708,1660,1686]" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref5329" refString="Lehtinen, P. T. (1981) Spiders of the Oriental-Australian region. III. Tetrablemmidae, with a world revision. Acta Zoologica Fennica, 162, 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="1981">Lehtinen, 1981</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
; however, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1873" box="[828,975,1660,1686]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Tetrablemma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[828,975,1660,1686]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">Tetrablemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be separated from the other two genera by having a distinctive abdominal plate arrangement and well-developed lateral horns of the vulva. Chelicerae of male and female 
<taxonomicName authorityName="O. Pickard-Cambridge" authorityYear="1873" box="[375,522,1732,1758]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Tetrablemma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[375,522,1732,1758]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">Tetrablemma</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are dimorphic; males have large and long cheliceral frontal horns, which are less developed and anterolaterally placed in females. Cheliceral horns are also present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Lin &amp; Li, 2014" authorityName="Lin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2014" box="[1104,1389,1768,1794]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Sinamma" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1104,1208,1768,1794]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">Sinamma</emphasis>
Lin &amp; Li, 2014
</taxonomicName>
, but this genus can be distinguished by the presence of a tubercle on the male carapace, although this character is also present in 
<taxonomicName authority="Lin &amp; Li, 2014" authorityName="Lin &amp; Li" authorityYear="2014" box="[268,610,1840,1866]" class="Arachnida" family="Tetrablemmidae" genus="Tetrablemma" kingdom="Animalia" order="Araneae" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="menglaensis">
<emphasis box="[268,433,1840,1866]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="93">T. menglaensis</emphasis>
Lin &amp; Li, 2014
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Lehtinen, P. T." box="[625,799,1840,1866]" pageId="1" pageNumber="93" pagination="1 - 151" refId="ref5329" refString="Lehtinen, P. T. (1981) Spiders of the Oriental-Australian region. III. Tetrablemmidae, with a world revision. Acta Zoologica Fennica, 162, 1 - 151." type="journal article" year="1981">Lehtinen, 1981</bibRefCitation>
; Lin &amp; Li, 2014).
</paragraph>
